originalText.text: My friend recommended JEaesthetics to me for laser, and I'm so happy with my treatments! I was so nervous going in, but Jackie made me feel comfortable and at home during my sessions. Besides for just working on my hair, she also gave me expert advice, recommendations, and products for my problem skin (and even shared some of her AMAZING collagen ointment that she makes herself). I'm super happy with the laser results, and my skin texture is better than ever. Would definitely recommend!!!

originalText.text: Jackie is amazing! I have been seeing her for 4 years and my skin has never looked better. I have done laser hair removal, laser genesis and peels. She even lightened a dark scar line on my arm for my wedding and it completely disappeared. I never get break outs and my skin looks healthy even through winter! Highly recommend.

originalText.text: I usually don’t leave negative reviews but I had to post my experience as a warning for prospective customers. Jackie is very unprofessional. To start, I purchased a Groupon deal for two face peels. The first face peel she applied was a weaker version that didn’t peel at all. The second stronger version (the one that should’ve initially been used) was essentially what I paid for. Pretty much got scammed out of the Groupon deal. I then went ahead and purchased a laser hair removal deal directly from her. Big mistake because she burned me. BIPOC be wary because we are not test subjects. She did not apply any gel to my chin area. If I could upload the photos to this review you will be horrified. My wife warned me several times not to go back but I always give people the benefit of the doubt (yes, even after I was burned). I then had an upcoming appointment where she contacted me and asked me to come in earlier because she had a communion party to attend. Later on that same day, she then contacted me to cancel the appointment because her cat died. Not to be apathetic but it just seemed too coincidental. Ultimately, enough was enough and I requested a refund for the remainder of the scheduled treatments. She indicated that she would send it but I have yet to receive it. I had to do a chargeback with my bank. Very poor experience and again, she is very unprofessional. Avoid at all costs!
